briefdescription.para: Copy-Constructor - create a NEW TimeTrack:: which is an independent copy of the original.

detaileddescription.para:
Calls TimeTrack::Init() to copy the track metadata, then does a bunch of manipulations on the Envelope:: and Ruler:: members in order to copy one to the other - unfortunately both lack a copy-constructor to encapsulate this.
orig
The original track to copy from

inbodydescription.para: : Give Envelope:: a copy-constructor instead of this?
: Give Ruler:: a copy-constructor instead of this?

briefdescription.para: Compute the integral warp factor between two non-warped time points.

detaileddescription.para:
Calculate the relative length increase of the chosen segment from the original sound. So if this time track has a low value (i.e. makes the sound slower), the NEW warped sound will be longer than the original sound, so the return value of this function is larger.
t0
The starting time to calculate from
t1
The ending time to calculate to
The relative length increase of the chosen segment from the original sound.

briefdescription.para: Compute the duration (in seconds at playback) of the specified region of the track.

detaileddescription.para:
Takes a region of the time track (specified by the unwarped time points in the project), and calculates how long it will actually take to play this region back, taking the time track's warping effects into account.
t0
unwarped time to start calculation from
t1
unwarped time to stop calculation at
the warped duration in seconds

briefdescription.para: Compute how much unwarped time must have elapsed if length seconds of warped time has elapsed.

parameterdescription.para: The unwarped time (seconds from project start) at which to start
How many seconds of warped time went past.

simplesect.para: The end point (in seconds from project start) as unwarped time

briefdescription.para: Copy the metadata from another track but not the points.

detaileddescription.para:
Copies the Name, DefaultName, Range and Display data from the source track
